obalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#330000>(7/15/03 9:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=297.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Cripple</span><hr size=1> I really never used the spell much because I did not believe it made much of a difference. My thoughts changed the other night. Was killing yard trash in PoN with my wife who is a druid. A guild member wanted to join us so we said sure. She is a 53 Monk. I pull with slow and root mob at spot. Mob gets snared and DoTed while the Monk attacks. The monk gets hit HARD and Druid needs to heal 3 to 4 times during the fight.<br>
I look thru my spell book to see what I could cast that would help and see Cripple. I think why not give it a shot. Pull a MoB and get it ready for kill. This time when Monk engages she does not seem to be getting hit as hard or as much. Pull another and same. Druid only needs to heal once or very rarely twice a fight now.<br>
I have also cast when we have a 61 Warrior with us but it is hard to tell if it makes much difference. His AC is 300 more than the Monk and he has at least twice as many HP.<br>
I think this spell will get more use from me in the future.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bregaladlow>Bregalad LoW</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Member</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#330000>(7/15/03 11:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=297.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cripple</span><hr size=1> Cripple has a huge Dex penalty - and Dex plays a large role in landing your blows.  It is especially useful against mobs that proc.   Also, Cripple lowers Agi and raw AC - which makes mob easier to hit, and lowers its mitigation potential. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bregalad Alcarin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, High Elf Phantasmist, Xev &lt;Legends of Westwood&gt;<br>
